cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.GR

This paper involves computer vision techniques for predicting 3D organ shape from 2D topogram images, which falls under the scope of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a generative model also suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) may be relevant sub-categories. Additionally, the application of this technique to medical imaging and the use of user annotations suggest that medical imaging (cs.MED) and graphics (cs.GR) may also be relevant sub-categories.
